#repost @iamcharrlottededavis
<<<< press play>>>> 2018 has been turning point for women’s rights with movements such as #metoo, time’s up and the gender pay gap gaining international momentum and pervading the highest echelons of society, show business and politics.
a light has certainly been shined on inequality, but we must now take the torch and shine that light further, bringing to light the lesser known challenges that the female gender battles on a daily basis, particularly those from social or economically disadvantaged backgrounds, whose voices might never be loud enough to land across the front pages.
international day of the girl child is that torch, and our contribution to this great cause paves the way for that light to shine brighter. it is an opportunity to celebrate girls and young women from a tender age, so that their future can be shaped and they can be given the opportunities to become the women they aspire to be. it was indeed a happy international day of the girl child! thank you to @lilfortescue  @iamamyjackson and all our sponsors @isawitfirst @bentleymotors @overfinch @seksywatches @lafrenchvodka_com @bimberdistillery @theritzlondon @boogieinwonderland @majmusic @chantallelaurent @michaelbosacki @emmajensendj @jjonessax 🎊🎉 #theidgc #plentymoretocome. my sincerest love to all of the people that made this evening possible and rallied together for a greater good and greater cause. you are forever in my heart x @weare23d what a production team!!! @txivgo 💫 @urban_caprice for the superb dining experience. #femalesaregod’smostpreciouscreationthankyoumom  #dannyminnick

text: my soul has a hat  i counted my years & realized that i have less time to live by,  than i have lived so far.  i feel like a child who won a pack of candies: at first he ate them with pleasure  but when he realized that there was little left, he began to taste them intensely.  i have no time for endless meetings where the statutes, rules, procedures & internal regulations are discussed,  knowing that nothing will be done.  i no longer have the patience  to stand absurd people who, despite their chronological age,  have not grown up.  my time is too short:  i want the essence,  my spirit is in a hurry.  i do not have much candy in the package anymore.  i want to live next to humans,  very realistic people who know how to laugh at their mistakes, who are not inflated by their own triumphs & who take responsibility for their actions. in this way, human dignity is defended  and we live in truth and honesty.  it is the essentials that make life useful. i want to surround myself with people who know how to touch the hearts of those whom hard strokes of life have learned to grow with sweet touches of the soul.  yes, i'm in a hurry. i'm in a hurry to live with the intensity that only maturity can give. i do not intend to waste any of the remaining desserts.  i am sure they will be exquisite,  much more than those eaten so far. my goal is to reach the end satisfied  and at peace with my loved ones and my conscience.  we have two lives & the second begins when you realize you only have one. •mario de andrade (san paolo 1893-1945) poet, novelist, essayist and musicologist. brazilian modernist •asl notebooks, 2018 @asleninde @sonalsoodphotography

text: my soul has a hat  i counted my years & realized that i have less time to live by,  than i have lived so far.  i feel like a child who won a pack of candies: at first he ate them with pleasure  but when he realized that there was little left, he began to taste them intensely.  i have no time for endless meetings where the statutes, rules, procedures & internal regulations are discussed,  knowing that nothing will be done.  i no longer have the patience  to stand absurd people who, despite their chronological age,  have not grown up.  my time is too short:  i want the essence,  my spirit is in a hurry.  i do not have much candy in the package anymore.  i want to live next to humans,  very realistic people who know how to laugh at their mistakes, who are not inflated by their own triumphs & who take responsibility for their actions. in this way, human dignity is defended  and we live in truth and honesty.  it is the essentials that make life useful. i want to surround myself with people who know how to touch the hearts of those whom hard strokes of life have learned to grow with sweet touches of the soul.  yes, i'm in a hurry. i'm in a hurry to live with the intensity that only maturity can give. i do not intend to waste any of the remaining desserts.  i am sure they will be exquisite,  much more than those eaten so far. my goal is to reach the end satisfied  and at peace with my loved ones and my conscience.  we have two lives & the second begins when you realize you only have one. •mario de andrade (san paolo 1893-1945) poet, novelist, essayist and musicologist. brazilian modernist •asl notebooks, 2018 @asleninde @sonalsoodphotography

text: my soul has a hat  i counted my years & realized that i have less time to live by,  than i have lived so far.  i feel like a child who won a pack of candies: at first he ate them with pleasure  but when he realized that there was little left, he began to taste them intensely.  i have no time for endless meetings where the statutes, rules, procedures & internal regulations are discussed,  knowing that nothing will be done.  i no longer have the patience  to stand absurd people who, despite their chronological age,  have not grown up.  my time is too short:  i want the essence,  my spirit is in a hurry.  i do not have much candy in the package anymore.  i want to live next to humans,  very realistic people who know how to laugh at their mistakes, who are not inflated by their own triumphs & who take responsibility for their actions. in this way, human dignity is defended  and we live in truth and honesty.  it is the essentials that make life useful. i want to surround myself with people who know how to touch the hearts of those whom hard strokes of life have learned to grow with sweet touches of the soul.  yes, i'm in a hurry. i'm in a hurry to live with the intensity that only maturity can give. i do not intend to waste any of the remaining desserts.  i am sure they will be exquisite,  much more than those eaten so far. my goal is to reach the end satisfied  and at peace with my loved ones and my conscience.  we have two lives & the second begins when you realize you only have one. •mario de andrade (san paolo 1893-1945) poet, novelist, essayist and musicologist. brazilian modernist •asl notebooks, 2018. @asleninde @sonalsoodphotography

text:
wcc press meet: ns madhavan hints #metoo disclosure

writer ns madhavan has pointed out that there is a possibility for the metoo campaign, which has shaken the hollywood and bollywood film industry, to reach malayalam.  he has tweeted in the light of the press meet to be held by the women in cinema collective (wcc) members on saturday evening.

he wrote that journalists should never miss today’s wcc press meet at ernakulam press club at 4 pm. ‘a little bird says this could be big,’ he wrote. he has put the #metoo hashtag on the post and that’s the point which arouses curiosity. stars including revathy, padmapriya and parvathy are attending the press meet

for more news and video updates, subscribe to www.english.mathrubhumi.com 
#mathrubhumi #latestkeralanews #newsupdates #photos #videos #instanews #dailyupdates #amma #wcc #metoo #movienews

text:
utilizo las  para orientarte. a través del tarot puedo saber qué está ocurriendo en tu vida e incluso lo que pasó en tu pasado.

creo que es importante comprobar la calidad de la vidente que tienes a la otra parte del teléfono. es vital la confianza entre tú vidente o tarotista y tú para la buena conexión y desarrollo de la consulta.

lógicamente no es fácil confiar en alguien que no conoces, por esta razón creo que es importante que la tarotista a la que consultar, sobre todo por primera vez, sea capaz de hablarte del pasado, ya que así se creará un vínculo de confianza entre la tarotista y tú.

text:
¿necesitas solucionar tus temas sentimentales? ¿tienes dudas que no te dejan descansar? algo te dice que un problema en tu relación; ¿una tercera persona quizás?… o bien que ya no está enamorado de ti. no sabes que pensar y, ni mucho menos, como actuar para disipar estas dudas. no sufras más, estás aquí por el destino y yo puedo ayudarte. la duda de si te quiere o no, si va a dar el paso hacia una relación seria, o bien si solo está jugando contigo, son preguntas que te generan inseguridad e inquietud. no te dejan ser tu misma y temes meter la pata en esta relación que tanto deseas. no te preocupes, yo voy a darte las respuestas que tanto necesitas. ¿te preocupa tu futuro? yo te lo cuento.

jag blåser i visselpipan för glatta livet! 🙋 #släppskammen

#repost @elaineeksvard (@get_repost)
・・・
när ett barn blir våldtaget av sin pappa, morfar eller som i 90% av fallen - en nära manlig anhörig. när en kvinna utsätta för sexuella övergrepp. förövarens bästa vän är tystnaden och värsta fienden är visselblåsaren! låt oss alla bli visselblåsare, tack @lulucartersweden för du satte bollen i rullning! jag älskar dig! 
#repost @lulucartersweden with @get_repost

text:
she is secondary, she is prime,
she is both at the same time.

she is gold, she is dust,
she is love, she is lust.

she is tough, she is mild,
she is calm, she is wild.

she is head, she is toe,
she is joy, she is woe.

she is beginning, she is end,
she is enemy, she is friend.

she is wildfire, she is ice,
she is desire, she is surprise.

she is grace, she is rage,
she is outstanding, she is average.

she is scar, she is star,
she is peace, she is war.

she is bitter, she is sour,
she is holy, she is pure.

she is barren, she is fertile,
she is both at the same time.
.
.
.
©anjali @uncaged_emotions_

an anonymous story from #akola.

text:
i am glad women are coming out as a beast! 
every now and then in bus, train, metro, cafe, college, digital world, almost everywhere we are touched, mentally raped, sexted, stared by someone and we don't even know their identity, who to be blame then? "man karta tha usne jo kia, uske liye uska sar phodd dun" even i have said this phrase thousand times in my entire life but i never took a stand i never discussed about this from anyone except my friends because i was afraid "ki badla lene ke liye isne isse kuch zyada kar diya to"? people are saying that why are you remembering or telling this after so many years. no, we do think about it every single day but didn't have the courage to bare it in front of the world. you know, when something happens like this, we get numb our reflex action stops working, that how can anyone behave like this? now, we've tolerated/ignored enough, we are game to make our reflex actions stronger, so beware! moreover, i request women/men/others to not misuse this wave to fulfill your personal agenda. #shecan #metoo #metooindia #metoomovement #iamgame #stronger #beware #baretruth #zerotolerance #dontignore #thoughtoftheday #notanymore #tfif

text:
maya’s legacy by vean ima
#blackhistorymonth day 13 ✍🏾🖤
*swipe left for spoken word*
.
.
when i grow up i wanna be just like you
synonymous with magic, rhyme and overflowing indelible truths. 
maya angelou award 
winning weaver of words.
i’d listen to you all day over the melody of the birds.
from whence did all your 
wisdom come?
i pour over your work and i’m left undone but emotionally and intellectually i’m left so alive!
by the honest depictions 
your pen never hides. ‘i rise’, ‘i know why a caged bird sings’
do you know what empowerment your gift from heaven brings?
because of you there can be a me,
the black female poet, your legacy. .
.
📸/ pinterest 🎵/ music composed by jonny easton

text_retweet:
#repost @ravishkumarndtv #moinqureshilg 
मेरा अकबर महान ! इस्तीफ़े से आगे के हैं सवाल 
सवाल अकबर के इस्तीफ़े का नहीं है। इस्तीफ़ा लेकर कोई महान नहीं बन जाएगा। वो तो होगा ही। मगर जवाब देना पडेगा कि इस अकबर में क्या ख़ूबी थी कि राज्य सभा का सदस्य बनाया, बीजेपी का सदस्य बनाया और मंत्री बनाया? इसके दो दो दलों के अंदरखाने तक पहुँचने और सत्ता तंत्र का बादशाह बन जाता है। आराम से कांग्रेस का सांसद, आराम से भाजपा का सांसद। क्या प्रधानमंत्री ने अकबर को मंत्री बनाते समय अपना होमवर्क नहीं किया था? यह कैसे हो सकता है? उन्हें बताना चाहिए कि क्या वाक़ई अपने राजनीतिक जीवन में वे अकबर के अंतरंग क़िस्सों से अनजान थे? दुनिया को बेटी बचाओ बेटी पढ़ाओ का संदेश दे रहे थे और ख़ुद अकबर बचाओ अकबर बढ़ाओ में लगे थे? नौ महिला पत्रकारों ने आरोप लगाए हैं। क्या यह भी संयोग है कि फ़ेसबुक पर अकबर पर मेरी पोस्ट धीमी कर दी गई है? हिन्दी अख़बारों के कई ज़िला संस्करणों से अकबर की ख़बर ग़ायब है? जिन हिन्दी अख़बारों में अकबर के कारनामे छपे हैं उनमें किसी महिला पत्रकार की आपबीती विस्तार से नहीं है। एक अकबर के लिए इतना सबकुछ। अकबर के इस्तीफ़े की ख़बर आती होगी लेकिन सोशल मीडिया और मीडिया में ख़बरें रोक कर और साधारण बनाने के पीछे कौन है? #ndtv #delhi #metoo #media

text:
"i was eleven or twelve years old and it was holi. i was waiting for my friend outside her house at around 8:30 pm when he came from behind. he used to visit her house for work. he had gulaal in his hand which he forcibly put on my face. i began screaming, but he covered my face and touched my breasts before running away.

after that, i was very scared of not only him, but every man. the feeling was so heavy that i didn't even tell my parents. i was so scared that i stopped going outside. it took me a really long time to get back to my usual life. i wasted two years of my life and haven't played holi since." if you have also faced street sexual harassment, please share your story with us. #hewonttease

text: i've posted this before but it seems like some of you men out there need a reminder. it's been a particularly difficult week to be a woman in this world; on a personal note, it's been a particularly difficult week to be a woman in my skin. this week i was cornered by two men in 7-11 in the middle of the day after being shamelessly objectified; i was charged at by a man as he repeatedly called me "fucking bitch" and videotaped me as i backed up in fear (for simply asking him to leave the private property that he was filming his skate video on); i was mocked and ridiculed by a group of men in a wine bar who were arguing that women should not be upset when male strangers ask them to smile on the street; i was cat called at least a dozen times while walking to and from work; i was approached 3 times while walking to and from work by men who thought it would make my day better if they tell me how good i look or simply exclaim "damnnn" as they unmistakably undress me with their eyes. all of this has stirred up emotions from past traumatic events that i really, really don't want to feel again. i'm ashamed to admit this week has almost defeated my spirit. i'm tempted to hide in the safety of my locked apartment, away from the gawking and the "accidental" brush ups and the dehumanizing words. instead, i will look the bullshit of our patriarchal society in the eyes and i'll challenge it; with the help of fellow strong women, i'll be a contributor of its demise. 💪🏼💪🏽💪🏾💪🏿 special shout out to the beautiful men out there who love us, protect us, defend us, respect us, support us as we fight our fight. you are seen and you are so very appreciated. ❤️ #downwiththepatriarchy #strongwomen #patriarchy #patriarchalsociety #donttellmetosmile #believewomen #supportwomen #feminism #intersectionalfeminism #metoo #gratefulforthemenoutthere

text:
중학생 시절, 야동을 보내주면 수행평가 점수를 올려주기로 유명한 옆 학교 선생이 있었다. 고등학교에서는 수업시간에 일부려 교단에 걸터앉아 책상 아래로 보이던 우리들의 다리를 훔쳐보던 선생이 있었다. 모욕적이고 불쾌했으나, 어떻게 문제제기를 해야할 지 몰랐고, 그저 친구들과 그 선생 변태같다며 조심하자는 이야기 하는것이 우리의 대처법 전부였다.  시대가 바뀌었다. 이제 많은 여학생들이 이와 같은 성추행을 참지 않는다. 참을 필요가 없다는 것을 알았기 때문이다. 스쿨미투 이야기를 하고, 학교에서 페미니즘 발표를 하고 에스엔에스에 탈코르셋을 이야기한다. 시대가 바뀌었다. 아이들은, 여성은 더 이상 참지 않는다. .
.
여러분은 옳습니다. 작은 외침들이 모여서 세계를 바꿀 수 있다고 나는 믿습니다. 여러분의 연대와 용기에 감사합니다. 지지하겠습니다. 듣겠습니다. 같이 분노하겠습니다.
.
.
#metoo #스쿨미투 #미투

text:
#bollywood has been making waves over the past few weeks with high-profile men being accused of being abusers and #metoo gaining strength. can people really continue accusing women of simply trying to seek attention when they finally find the strength to reveal harrowing experiences? many of the accusers are women with successful career graphs who are in no need of media mileage or attention. why would they speak out and why would other, equally successful women, add their voices to their plights, sharing their own experiences?
why would women take on well-loved industry long-timers - #nanapatekar, #subashghai, #vikasbahl, #rajatkapoor, #aloknath, #abhijeetbhattqcharya, #sajidkhan, #karimmorani - unless there was truth to their stories?
and why are so many of us, with our bollywood obsessions, not acknowledging this change that’s taking place? could this change extend borders and lead to more high-profile pakistani women also raising their voices against abusers, the ones we all hear whispers about but continue to be lauded as our heroes, even icons? could this wave of change lead to greater gender sensitivity and more respect for women? better work environments? open mindedness? 
so proud of @dawn_images and my editor, @hamnazubair for taking a stand when so many hedged away - uncomfortable or hiding their friends? - and for encouraging women to raise their voices when they are wronged. #saynotoabuse #windsofchange #imagesdawn

text:
i wrote this story long before the "me too" movement started trending. considering the sensitive nature of the subject, i made a few guys i thought were pretty suave and well read, review it. you know, just to test the waters, being the cautious person that i am. needless to say that it was met with disdain and derisive comments like " oh, so if you change your mind it's the guys fault? eh?". well, yes it is, because mutual consent is as basic as brushing your teeth to ward off an aversive stink. if you don't (brush your teeth) you aren't just unhygenic, you become repulsive. ever since the "metoo" movement has spread like fire, you can't help but see condescending comments of people dismissing women like they are a bunch of disruptive flies focusing on crap. that's when i decided to publish this story just to create awareness amongst people about consent and the alarmingly rampant rape culture in the world today. if you support it, share it to serve the purpose it was penned down for.

p.s - to read the story please click on the link in bio 👆👆

do you know if you're being abused?
or
do you even realize you are an abuser?

text:
#metoo

a storm is stirring as your voices resonate with your echoes ,
a cyclone which took root from beneath the whirlpool of your skirt,
your time has come.

i am so proud of all the women who are speaking up. of all the men who are behind the screens holding their hands. the hazy curtain that hides ugliness of our society , and unfortunately is reinforced by victim's own hushed whispers ,is finally being pulled down. we need backlash,we need anger,we need the screaming and we need to not ever again let anyone push us  down.

women who are speaking up are women who have found themselves and who have realised that before today they were buried. to these courageous and beautiful women,i implore .go a step further and seek recourse of law . whether it was 10 years ago,20 years ago it doesn't matter. make a complaint. show the little girls the power of community. when you take this step further you shake the state into realising that it bears a responsibility towards you because it does. our constitution guarantees us the respect and dignity ,of life and liberty . there are girls with stories that would never reach us because they don't have the power of social media. for them go a step further.

another reason why this next step is essential is because there are people who will misuse this movement . this movement is empowering and don't forget that the only reason, the person who violated you ,did so because he was given a power over you.by the society,the industry,your family.

dont let anyone misuse the empowerment to violate somebody else.don't empower people who don't understand it's responsibility. it is natural justice that every person should be heard ,even the monster who did this to you . 
and lastly ,

thank you for showing me that there is power in community and i am not alone.

#metoo #againstinjustice
#writersofinstagram
#writingforcause

ये जो me too कम्पैन चल रहा है इसे हल्के में मत लीजिये - उस व्यक्ति के आला दिमाग की दाद दीजिये जिसके हरामी मष्तिष्क से ये निकला है कि कुछ बूढी होती कोठे की मौसियों का भी वापस बाजार भाव बढ़ा दिया है - ऊपर से खतरनाक पक्ष क्या है -समझे आप? जो कलम राष्ट्रवादिता के समर्थन में लिखेगी उसका चरित्र हनन किया जाएगा -ये सीधे थ्रेट हैं - ब्लैकमेल है। अब इस कैम्पेन से थोड़ा डरिये भी और इसका तोड़ भी सोचिये , क्योंकि बहुतो की कलम खामोश हो जाएगी। बहुतो की पत्नियाँ समझदार नहीं निकलेंगी और परिवार तबाह कर बैठेंगी - पुरुष मूर्खो की तरह खड़ा रह जाएगा। और जो ये चूकी हुई नगर वधुऐं मी-टू कैम्पेन चला रही है

जिनकी बाज़ारी कीमत ५ रुपया भी नहीं है - इनको कोर्ट में घसीटने की तैयारी कीजिये - लड़िये पलट वार कीजिये इन वेश्याओं पर - इनको नारी होने लाभ मत लेने दीजिये -- याद रखिये ''ताड़का - शूर्पणखा-- पूतना '' भी नारियाँ ही थी, जिन्हे मारने मे ईश्वर ने भी देर न लगाई.

हालीवुड और विदेशों का चलन #meetoo का भसड़ अब भारत भी आ गया ..लेकिन निशाने पर कौन है ये सोचिये.... एमजे अकबर 13 सालो तक नरेन्द्र मोदी और बीजेपी के सबसे बड़े आलोचक थे ।। मोदी के खिलाफ खूब जहर उगलते थे । तब उन पर किसी भी महिला ने कोई आरोप नही लगाया .. लेकिन जैसे ही वो मोटा भाई के आबे जमजम से पवित्र हो गए और केंद्रीय मंत्री बन गए तो अब चुनावी वर्ष में 5 महिला पत्रकार उनके ऊपर आरोप लगा रही हैं कि उन्होंने कई बार उन्हें गलत तरीके से छुआ था 
मतलब जब इन महिलाओं को छुआ था तब उन्हें नहीं पता चला कि उन्हें सही तरीके से छुआ जा रहा है कि गलत तरीके से लेकिन 20 साल 25 साल बाद अचानक इन महिलाओं को याद आने लगा फलाने ने उन्हें गलत तरीके से छुआ था 
अब नाना पाटेकर और विवेक अग्निहोत्री जैसे लोगों को देख लीजिए यह लोग ट्विटर पर और दूसरे माध्यमों में वामपंथियों को जमकर लतियाते हैं उनके खिलाफ अचानक दो तीन महिलाएं सामने आती हैं और कहती है 25 साल पहले मेरे साथ ही उन्होंने गलत व्यवहार किया था 
यह एक नया ट्रेंड जो बेहद खतरनाक है अब 20 साल पहले या 25 साल पहले ना तो कोई सुबूत बचा होगा ना ही कोई ऐसा गवाह बचा बचा होगा फिर अब आरोप लगाकर वह भी ट्विटर पर या फेसबुक पर वह महिला क्या हासिल करना चाहती है 
एक और ट्रेंड मैंने देखा है कि ज्यादातर वही महिलाएं आरोप लगा रही है या तो जिनका घर टूट चुका है या जो वक्त की मार से बेहद मोटी और कुरूप हो चुकी है और ऐसे पुरुषों पर आरोप लगा रही हैं जो अब शांत सुखी दांपत्य जीवन बिता रहे हैं #meeto #meto #meetoo #metoo
पुरुषों के लिए #youto #

जो कलम राष्ट्रवादिता के समर्थन में लिखेगी उसका चरित्र हनन किया जाएगा -ये सीधे थ्रेट हैं - ब्लैकमेल है। अब इस कैम्पेन से थोड़ा डरिये भी और इसका तोड़ भी सोचिये , क्योंकि बहुतो की कलम खामोश हो जाएगी। बहुतो की पत्नियाँ समझदार नहीं निकलेंगी और परिवार तबाह कर बैठेंगी - पुरुष मूर्खो की तरह खड़ा रह जाएगा। और जो ये चूकी हुई नगर वधुऐं मी-टू कैम्पेन चला रही है जिनकी बाज़ारी कीमत ५ रुपया भी नहीं है - इनको कोर्ट में घसीटने की तैयारी कीजिये - लड़िये पलट वार कीजिये इन वेश्याओं पर - इनको नारी होने लाभ मत लेने दीजिये -- याद रखिये `` ताड़का - शूर्पणखा -- पूतना `` भी नारियाँ ही थी , जिन्हे मारने मे ईश्वर ने भी देर न लगाई . हालीवुड और विदेशों का चलन का भसड़ अब भारत भी आ गया ..लेकिन निशाने पर कौन है ये सोचिये ... . एमजे अकबर 13 सालो तक नरेन्द्र मोदी और बीजेपी के सबसे बड़े आलोचक थे ।। मोदी के खिलाफ खूब जहर उगलते थे । तब उन पर किसी भी महिला ने कोई आरोप नही लगाया .. लेकिन जैसे ही वो मोटा भाई के आबे जमजम से पवित्र हो गए और केंद्रीय मंत्री बन गए तो अब चुनावी वर्ष में 5 महिला पत्रकार उनके ऊपर आरोप लगा रही हैं कि उन्होंने कई बार उन्हें गलत तरीके से छुआ था मतलब जब इन महिलाओं को छुआ था तब उन्हें नहीं पता चला कि उन्हें सही तरीके से छुआ जा रहा है कि गलत तरीके से लेकिन 20 साल 25 साल बाद अचानक इन महिलाओं को याद आने लगा फलाने ने उन्हें गलत तरीके से छुआ था अब नाना पाटेकर और विवेक अग्निहोत्री जैसे लोगों को देख लीजिए यह लोग ट्विटर पर और दूसरे माध्यमों में वामपंथियों को जमकर लतियाते हैं उनके खिलाफ अचानक दो तीन महिलाएं सामने आती हैं और कहती है 25 साल पहले मेरे साथ ही उन्होंने गलत व्यवहार किया था यह एक नया ट्रेंड जो बेहद खतरनाक है अब 20 साल पहले या 25 साल पहले ना तो कोई सुबूत बचा होगा ना ही कोई ऐसा गवाह बचा बचा होगा फिर अब आरोप लगाकर वह भी ट्विटर पर या फेसबुक पर वह महिला क्या हासिल करना चाहती है एक और ट्रेंड मैंने देखा है कि ज्यादातर वही महिलाएं आरोप लगा रही है या तो जिनका घर टूट चुका है या जो वक्त की मार से बेहद मोटी और कुरूप हो चुकी है और ऐसे पुरुषों पर आरोप लगा रही हैं जो अब शांत सुखी दांपत्य जीवन बिता रहे हैं etoo पुरुषों के लिए #

text:
if our gods can do it, why not us? why is it that a woman can’t emulate the nine forms of durga, namely—shailaputrī, brahmachārinī, chandraghanṭā, kuṣhmāndā, skandamātā, kātyāyanī, kālarātrī, mahāgaurī and siddhidātrī, in herself and unfold a new chapter in the history of creation. 
remember, like in the legends bygone, there will always be a demon making his way into our lives ( in different forms) but the spirit of not giving up and raising your voice when needed, can be laid with a solid foundation of belief.
ma durga wants to instill in every woman to grow with a feeling of triumph and faith that whatever the circumstances be, never think you are too weak or incapable of putting up a brave front.

#navratri2018 #womentoday #durgashakti

text:
05/31.
there is a thunderstorm going on. outside and within.

every 30 seconds or so, the lightning flashes and i don't flinch. not anymore.

i remember being 7, adorned with a red and blue little uniform, my hand clasped firmly in my mother's grasp. i remember flinching as the downpour drenched my uniform, making me shiver throughout the classes.

i remember being 10, walking the streets to fetch a vegetable to nourish our bodies. unknown faces and racing dogs accompanied me, i didn't flinch much. maybe a little.

then i was 15, clinging to a pole in the ever crowded city bus. sweltering bodies greeting and parting, i trembled. head to toe. 
before i knew it, i was 20. a woman, they said and i accepted. i was asked to run to the shelter of my abode before twilight lest men get in my way. 
did they know? did they? i always wondered. 
i'm 24 today. and i can't sleep. there have been nights when i have been forced to listen to snores of content as i lie there, twisting and turning. shutting my eyes close would invoke the demons, lurking close by. 
yet, everyday around 3, i drift off into a light sleep. eventually, morning comes around and when it does, the demons shy away. i stop flinching. the sunlight shining through the slits in the curtains always make me smile. and i thank the universe for hope. 
tomorrow, it's going to repeat. the tossing and turning, the insomnia, and the unending trains of thought. but, the sunlight is going to repeat, too. and as long as it does, the universe will guide me when i flinch. and that is enough. 
for now.

ps. stay blessed.

#metoo

text:
07/17.
the man she loved was gentle, touching with care, barely hurting. yet she screamed within, a howling of sorts.

the boy she befriended pulled her close, hugging her. agony was all she left.

her father kissed her forehead, all warmth and love. she flinched, a jolt of shock running down her spine.

they were oblivious, she was aware.

she was aware and eternally injured. injured at all those places his hands had travelled. injured at all those places he had grabbed, he had twisted, he had claimed to be his. the places he had believed were inane.

there was a time she had yearned for a touch, a touch that would sizzle the blood in her veins, a touch that would send shivers down her spine, a touch that would make her heart skip beats.

at the age of eleven, she got all she had yearned for. again and again. the blood in her veins sizzled, shivers bolted down her spine and her heart skipped one too many beats.

at the age of twenty four, it still did. in her nightmares. again and again.

the body he had claimed was inane enough to be trampled upon, had turned into a block of stone over time. bits and pieces of it rotting away, spoilt and desolate. it was now shriveled and worn out, peeling off at the edges like a block of wooden piece in a land lost deep beneath the sea.

not one, or two or three, but every other day did she wake up, shivering and lost, breathless and perspiring in the darkness. her breathing ragged, her body shuddering and her mind turning into jelly. and she would fear closing her tired eyes again for how many times could one be touched when not asked for?

the nights were consumed by nightmares unasked for and the days by phobia the years of caging in had developed. she no longer ambled the streets with no care in the world, or explored anyplace with no being by her side. a simple look by a passing by stranger turned into a suspicion arising due to mistrust. during these moments, she wondered if the man who touched her eleven year old self blatantly in his thirst for forbidden pleasure ever regretted it. (continued in next post). #metoo

text:
12/03.
it happened on a thursday night. i was on my way back from a dinner, pondering what my lesson plan for the next day was going to look like. i wasn't on defense because i had a friend around. i barely had my guard up. 
i felt a hand feel my hair, and tuck it behind my ear. carelessly. with ease and fearlessness. i turned around, facing the man. there's always this moment when you are abused, a single minuscule of time wherein every bit of your body freezes, your brain refusing to respond. i stared, eyes glazed out. 
he smiled at me. and his friend did too. 
then came the fear, the bone crunching fear of being a 12 year old trying to fight away the unwelcome touch. 
i demanded what did he think he was doing? and he tells me, very calmly, that he mistook me for a child. 
then came his series of apologies.

people around me tell me to let it go. rather, shut me up. it barely took them a minute or two to brush me aside.

scream was all i could do in that moment. that moment filled with panic, denial and shock. 
later came the thoughts. how easy it was for everyone to ask me to let it go? 
two days have gone by since that incident, here i'm, lying awake, for closed eyelids meant unending nightmares.

how many voices will you all shun, how many bodies will you all harm, how many lives will you all destroy? how many? 
maybe the internet screaming "me too" is the most humans can do to try and stop this cycle of destruction.
#metoo

text:
sometimes i think there’s no way i can make it to that next milestone. i can literally hear my thoughts talking me out of it. every excuse or justification to run. i think so many of you can relate when i say that no moment is harder than the one that happens just before the breakthrough. right before i level up, i am all consumed with fear and overwhelm. then there is choice. sometimes i’m not ready yet - and that’s all it is but it’s so hard not to make it mean i failed.
and then other times it’s 💥. everything you are going through is preparing you for the life you truly want to live.
name: Hello Divorce
tweet_full:

and then other times it’s 💥. everything you are going through is preparing you for the life you truly want to live.

text: being a woman in any industry has never been an easy thing. for so long women have been made to feel inferior and weak by their male counterparts. in this industry if you don't give in to the personal wishes of the director or producer you're looked at as 'difficult to work with' or life on the set is intentionally made harder just because you chose to say "no". i have personally experienced this and i have been called a drama queen and someone with too much attitude. even to the extent of someone saying that i'm not from here and this is how things work in india. it reached a point where i decided to just keep my mouth shut and my thoughts to myself and accept the fact that women have no voice. and if they do say something then there are consequences for what they say. it's sad that the issues that were prevalent 10 years ago are still on going today. but thanks to social media women are finding their voices and finally speaking out. i encourage all women that have faced adversity to express themselves and know that we are all here to support each other. what happened to tanushree dutta wasn't right, we need to address it and take action. together. #metoo

text:
most days i'm a wood artist/woodworker...er... professional sawdust maker, but first and foremost, i'm a son/grandson/brother/brother-in-law/cousin/uncle/nephew to my family. i also consider myself a friend/mentor/advocate/ally/supporter/activist for a good part of my life as well. family and friends are of utmost importance to me and i wouldn't be who i am today without them. i especially owe a lot to all the strong women in my life. women like them face continued and new barriers that were thought to being gradually broken down. if the past few weeks or so in addition to the beginnings of the #metoo movement, have taught us anything, it's that women are still continually not being heard, believed, and respected, among others. feels more like 1918 than 2018.

amidst all the turmoil this country and the rest of the world is currently going through, socially and politically, the girls in my life still face a future full of opportunities and possibilities. my three nieces and soon-to-be fourth ("little shrimp" as my nephew, kenzo, calls her 🦐😂), mean the world to me. this year, mina, the oldest, turned 10, emmi, 6, and the youngest, isla turned 2 just last month. i unfortunately don't get to see them too often, but they're all growing up so fast! as their uncle, i only wish them the absolute best. i hope i can be there for them to support and fight for them in any which i can. i do my best to be as good of a role model as i can be too.

as but a humble man, i consider myself unashamedly a staunch feminist. i don't purport to be an expert by any means as i'm obviously not a woman, but i do my utmost best to understand what it's like to be a woman by hearing personal stories from the people in my life and reading about them. it's disheartening and unfortunate that still in 2018, girls and women still need to take to the streets to fight for their true unequivocal equality on all levels.

as but that single humble man, i'm doing my best to advocate and fight for the next generation of girls growing and coming up in society through the non-profit after school program that many of you know i've been volunteering for since 2010, the @sb_school_of_squash. continued ⬇️⬇

text:
thanks to me too campaign i have got courage to speak about my heartbreaking horrible incident happened with me on night of 6th aug with 73year old legend ,so called selfish friend “subhash ghai ” @subhashghai1 
i was living from very heavy heart and guilt from last 2 months  #deeplydestroyed.
incident happened was shock of my life.i lost respect and faith for people in film industry.
worst day of my life when we were at his home he told me to give him a massage , he kept my hand on his back and ear and told me to give me massage and than with respect of his age i did it , suddenly he pulled me on him, and tried to kiss me,and started putting his restless hands on my private body parts i really don’t know how i defended myself ,and pulled him away i told him that i have to go to birthday party please sir let me go ,and worst ,he challenged me if you will not come back today i will not work with you ,he said no matter it’s 3 4 5 am you have to come .
 his words were “ dekh le aaj ka din hain ,yaa toh aaj yaa toh kabhi nahi” i can make you star , aaj teri pariksha hain ..decide karle.. that mental torcher and  pressure on me he created that i was shivering and not able to think anything.
i withdrawn myself from that situation in shock.
same night he msgd me at 2.30am with the question mark of my coming back, than i msgd him with a scary heart that sir i can’t come.i m in severe headache.

and after this molestation he started ignoring ,he stopped answering calls and he stopped msging me. he proved that were all fake promises,he proved that my birthday party organised for me by him was also with wrong intensions. he told remove all our pics from social media because people will misunderstand our relation.

he proved that if 73 year old intelligent person do such things ,anyone can do..so where aspiring girls should go and where they can stand in this hindi cinema ,why these bloody cowards want a girl only for there penises .. can anyone please tell me ????
cried !! i was not able to tell this to anyone or my family. but today i felt i should speak and fight for my self respect. girls don’t trust anyone , create your own path. fight!
 feeling light @metoomvmt #metoo

text:
i stumbled upon this article today describing conditional love, the kind of love most of us know well.  unconditional love, on the other hand, is at the heart of yoga where we seek to fuel our self compassion and pacify our self hatred. this leads to a deeper love for humanity and care for others which is a far cry from our current political and economic system. it is the path to ending violence against humanity. when we compete with eachother we perpetuate selfish behaviour. part of the way we can extend our compassion is through the act of giving with no expectations or conditions.
.
"conditional love is a polarized emotion, meaning that it has an opposite emotion.  the opposite extreme of love is hatred. conditional love comes from ego and  generally focuses on someone (romantic partner, child, parent, friend). when we love someone conditionally, we tend to want them to look, act, and think in ways that fit our own paradigms and expectations.  we hold others accountable to our expectations in order to qualify for our affection.  if they act the way we want them to, we express our approval; if they act contrary to our wishes, we withhold our expression of acceptance of them, usually in some form of anger.  conditional love polarizes our internal thought process to believe, “i am right, and you are wrong, so i think you should see things my way.” as soon as we begin to judge someone as being right or wrong, it is our cue that we are not in a space of unconditional love because we are perceiving that we are the authority for someone else’s life.  this ultimately results in a power play for everyone involved because it focuses on control, which typically elicits a defensive reaction from the people whom we are trying to change.

unconditional love is neutral and has no opposite polarity. unconditional love is not something that happens to us or outside of us. the source of unconditional love is spirit; therefore it is available to everyone without discernment. it comes through to us at a soul level.  we make a conscious decision to choose thoughts based on unconditional love although this does not mean we agree with everyone or everything." ~ sandra brossman

text: #metoo: एमजे अकबर पर बोले अमित शाह- 'देखना पड़ेगा, ये सच है या गलत' metoo कैंपेन के तहत आ रहीं यौन शोषण की शिकायतों के बीच मोदी सरकार ने बड़ा फैसला लिया है. महिला और बाल विकास मंत्री मेनका गांधी ने metoo के तहत आए मामलों की जांच करने के लिए एक कमेटी गठित करने का ऐलान किया है.metoo कैंपेन के बाद एक्शन में आई मोदी सरकार ने जहां ऐसे मामलों की जांच के लिए कमेटी गठित करने का फैसला लिया है, वहीं इस कैंपेन की गिरफ्त में फंसे केंद्रीय मंत्री एमजे अकबर पर अब भारतीय जनता पार्टी के अध्यक्ष अमित शाह ने बयान दिया है. शाह ने अकबर पर लगे शोषण के आरोपों पर कहा है कि देखना पड़ेगा, ये सच हैं या गलत. उन्होंने कहा, 'देखना पड़ेगा कि यह सच हैं या गलत. हमें उस शख्स के पोस्ट की सत्यता जांचनी होगी, जिसने आरोप लगाए हैं. मेरा नाम इस्तेमाल करते हुए भी आप कुछ भी लिख सकते हैं.' हालांकि, इस मामले की जांच की जाएगी या नहीं, इस पर उन्होंने कोई ठोस जवाब नहीं दिया. लेकिन शाह ने इतना जरूर कहा कि 'इस पर जरूर सोचेंगे.' #metoo कैंपेन के तहत तमाम महिलाएं आपबीती शेयर कर रही हैं और बता रही हैं कि जीवन के किस हिस्से और किस वक्त में उन्हें यौन शोषण का शिकार पड़ा या उनसे काम के बदले फेवर मांगा गया. इसी कड़ी में कुछ महिला पत्रकारों ने मौजूदा केंद्रीय विदेश राज्य मंत्री और वरिष्ठ पत्रकार रहे एमजे अकबर के खिलाफ गंभीर इल्जाम लगाए हैं. केंद्रीय मंत्री पर लगातार सामने आ रहे आरोपों पर कांग्रेस घेराबंदी कर रही है. इस मामले में बीजेपी की चुप्पी भी सवाल उठाए जा रहे हैं, जिसके बीच अमित शाह का ये बयान सामने आया है. मोदी सरकार ने ऐसे मामलों की जांच के लिए एक कमेटी का भी गठन किया है. वरिष्ठ न्यायविद् और कानून के पेशे से जुड़े लोग इस कमेटी के मेंबर होंगे और सारे मामलों की जांच करेंगे. #news #politicalaffairsmedia #india @amitshahofficial @bjp4india

pre_proc_tweet: एमजे अकबर पर बोले अमित शाह- 'देखना पड़ेगा, ये सच है या गलत' metoo कैंपेन के तहत आ रहीं यौन शोषण की शिकायतों के बीच मोदी सरकार ने बड़ा फैसला लिया है. महिला और बाल विकास मंत्री मेनका गांधी ने metoo के तहत आए मामलों की जांच करने के लिए एक कमेटी गठित करने का ऐलान किया है.metoo कैंपेन के बाद एक्शन में आई मोदी सरकार ने जहां ऐसे मामलों की जांच के लिए कमेटी गठित करने का फैसला लिया है, वहीं इस कैंपेन की गिरफ्त में फंसे केंद्रीय मंत्री एमजे अकबर पर अब भारतीय जनता पार्टी के अध्यक्ष अमित शाह ने बयान दिया है. शाह ने अकबर पर लगे शोषण के आरोपों पर कहा है कि देखना पड़ेगा, ये सच हैं या गलत. उन्होंने कहा, 'देखना पड़ेगा कि यह सच हैं या गलत. हमें उस शख्स के पोस्ट की सत्यता जांचनी होगी, जिसने आरोप लगाए हैं. मेरा नाम इस्तेमाल करते हुए भी आप कुछ भी लिख सकते हैं.' हालांकि, इस मामले की जांच की जाएगी या नहीं, इस पर उन्होंने कोई ठोस जवाब नहीं दिया. लेकिन शाह ने इतना जरूर कहा कि 'इस पर जरूर सोचेंगे.'  कैंपेन के तहत तमाम महिलाएं आपबीती शेयर कर रही हैं और बता रही हैं कि जीवन के किस हिस्से और किस वक्त में उन्हें यौन शोषण का शिकार पड़ा या उनसे काम के बदले फेवर मांगा गया. इसी कड़ी में कुछ महिला पत्रकारों ने मौजूदा केंद्रीय विदेश राज्य मंत्री और वरिष्ठ पत्रकार रहे एमजे अकबर के खिलाफ गंभीर इल्जाम लगाए हैं. केंद्रीय मंत्री पर लगातार सामने आ रहे आरोपों पर कांग्रेस घेराबंदी कर रही है. इस मामले में बीजेपी की चुप्पी भी सवाल उठाए जा रहे हैं, जिसके बीच अमित शाह का ये बयान सामने आया है. मोदी सरकार ने ऐसे मामलों की जांच के लिए एक कमेटी का भी गठन किया है. वरिष्ठ न्यायविद् और कानून के पेशे से जुड़े लोग इस कमेटी के मेंबर होंगे और सारे मामलों की जांच करेंगे.
stop_filter_tweet: एमजे अकबर पर बोले अमित शाह- 'देखना पड़ेगा , ये सच है या गलत ' metoo कैंपेन के तहत आ रहीं यौन शोषण की शिकायतों के बीच मोदी सरकार ने बड़ा फैसला लिया है . महिला और बाल विकास मंत्री मेनका गांधी ने metoo के तहत आए मामलों की जांच करने के लिए एक कमेटी गठित करने का ऐलान किया है.metoo कैंपेन के बाद एक्शन में आई मोदी सरकार ने जहां ऐसे मामलों की जांच के लिए कमेटी गठित करने का फैसला लिया है , वहीं इस कैंपेन की गिरफ्त में फंसे केंद्रीय मंत्री एमजे अकबर पर अब भारतीय जनता पार्टी के अध्यक्ष अमित शाह ने बयान दिया है . शाह ने अकबर पर लगे शोषण के आरोपों पर कहा है कि देखना पड़ेगा , ये सच हैं या गलत . उन्होंने कहा , 'देखना पड़ेगा कि यह सच हैं या गलत . हमें उस शख्स के पोस्ट की सत्यता जांचनी होगी , जिसने आरोप लगाए हैं . मेरा नाम इस्तेमाल करते हुए भी आप कुछ भी लिख सकते हैं . ' हालांकि , इस मामले की जांच की जाएगी या नहीं , इस पर उन्होंने कोई ठोस जवाब नहीं दिया . लेकिन शाह ने इतना जरूर कहा कि 'इस पर जरूर सोचेंगे . ' कैंपेन के तहत तमाम महिलाएं आपबीती शेयर कर रही हैं और बता रही हैं कि जीवन के किस हिस्से और किस वक्त में उन्हें यौन शोषण का शिकार पड़ा या उनसे काम के बदले फेवर मांगा गया . इसी कड़ी में कुछ महिला पत्रकारों ने मौजूदा केंद्रीय विदेश राज्य मंत्री और वरिष्ठ पत्रकार रहे एमजे अकबर के खिलाफ गंभीर इल्जाम लगाए हैं . केंद्रीय मंत्री पर लगातार सामने आ रहे आरोपों पर कांग्रेस घेराबंदी कर रही है . इस मामले में बीजेपी की चुप्पी भी सवाल उठाए जा रहे हैं , जिसके बीच अमित शाह का ये बयान सामने आया है . मोदी सरकार ने ऐसे मामलों की जांच के लिए एक कमेटी का भी गठन किया है . वरिष्ठ न्यायविद् और कानून के पेशे से जुड़े लोग इस कमेटी के मेंबर होंगे और सारे मामलों की जांच करेंगे .

text:
when i became a teenager , there was an in build self respect in me. i always felt a need to protect my self in every situation. there was never even a thought that somebody else needs to protect me in danger. i looked upon to take care of my self at anytime. growing up, traveling around , meeting people especially men ,i can say having no fear inside me but love and kindness for the other gender has only helped me to meet amazing men.  we need to work within ourself a lot before we put the blame on the other gender . we need to take complete responsibility of our actions , our inactions, of our feelings. the inside work needs to happen much more within us before we point fingers at others. .
.

text:
just finished (pau) watching a star is born

went by myself (more deep thoughts if you decide to keep reading) wow!!! so many emotions/left in awe of the acting & singing talent! 
@ladygaga you are every female’s spirit animal!!!! you & @bradleycoopertv leave all of us in awe of your raw talent. you’re actors/performers in your own right but this is something special. 
i went to a celebration of life this morning, dropped my son off @ school for fall fest which was made clear that i was not invited to attend. hearing from girlfriends this movie would make me cry, i was ecstatic the theatre was pretty much empty. i hold it together so hard in everyday life, i break down easily in movies. i enjoy sharing any experience w/others but also don’t mind going solo. growing up an only child i’ve always had only me. as much of an old cliche romantic as i am, i’m also stubborn & independent. 
i love the line where ally says this is the only time i look for you. seriously🙌🏽i’ve given too many chances & power to others in the past. this time giving that chance but putting myself first. 
i also want to comment on @ladygaga for her interview on @colbertlateshow. (i’ve been recording any & all interviews she’s been on) thank you @ladygaga for your eloquent, precise, direct explanation of what happens in our brains when dealing w/sexual assault. 
i’ve experienced it my entire life. she is on-point. what do women do....we file it away somewhere in our filing system of a brain in order to move on & succeed. i have forgotten many memories, but unfortunately can recall every single time i was assaulted verbally or physically. 
i only recently stood up for myself & said to the person your actions are sickening, not wanted, not ok. fuck you!!!! you are raising young girls, my hope is that you raise them to respect themselves, know their self-worth & tell any man to fuck off when they cross the line. 
fulfilling life with our absolute best versions of ourselves & supporting other to do the same. 
@ladygaga thank you for helping me feel beautiful about my big italian nose. ❤️ #selflove  #selfacceptance #loveyourself #astarisborn #ladygaga #bradleycooper #metoo #momlife

text:
here is an ode to bollywood's messiah who has abandoned his 'angry young man' tenour at a time when #metoo is gaining momentum in india- . 
tu khud ki khoj mein nikal
tu kis liye chup-chaap hai?
tu bol! tere ‘silene’ se
poori society hataash hai
poori society hataash hai

jo tujhse lipte privileges hain
samajh na isko vastra tu

jo teri jhoothi campaigns hai
samajh na in ko shastra tu

ye privileges pighaal ke
bana le inko shastra tu
bana le inko shastra tu!

tu khud ki khoj me nikal
tu kis liye chup chaap hai?

charitra jab pavitra hai
to kyu hai ye dasha teri
‘consent’ ki baat karte ho
to kyu hai ab chuppi teri?

ye politicians ko haq nahi
ki chheene amisha teri
ki chheene amisha teri

tu khud ki khoj me nikal..
tu kis liye chup chaap hai?

tu politicial pawn nhi
tu ‘angry young man’ hai

tu opportunistic nhi
tu laakho ke liye misaal hai
tu laakho ke liye misaal hai

tu khud ki khoj mei nikal
tu kis liye chup chaap hai

tu chal! tere ‘anger’ ki
#metoo ko talaash hai
#metoo ko talaash hai

text:
#metoo is not an attack on men, it is not something one should be scared of, but rather embrace it.
it is not about how cruel the past has been, it is about a safer present & a sustainable future, a movement that lights up the possibility of changing rugged traditions & mindsets in our still patriarchal society. it is about empowering the shakti & accepting change by coming together as a community.
silence, although understandable, had its cost. for a long time, most women defined their own sexual harassment and assault as something unspoken, something private, something to be ashamed of acknowledging. but times have changed & so have women, now stronger than ever.
this year as we welcome the warrior goddess, the protector from evils and demonic forces 'durga'. lets learn to respect the real ones, the ones that we deem vulnerable & weak. i urge the men out there not to judge or make jokes & memes about it, just listen, there are many prayers that are still to be heard, and to the women, you are not alone, you never were. its time for your point of view.

text:
i have ptsd from childhood.
cast aside by a clergy who values dogma over empathy.
my abuser at 12 will never pay for his crimes, while i deal with ptsd everyday.

but you know what?

i have empathy, a warrior's heart, and deeply inspired to keep up the good.

if you have #ptsd, taking care of yourself is essential. you'll run slower, but think deeper.

you'll have good months, and bad months.

more the reason to live your life free from toxic people.

and even if you can do nothing to solve a problem, remember worry does not help. love yourself, soothe yourself.

running ragged will just make it worse. you became strong but hold your cup up high, because your empathy and thirst for others being treated with a high conscious quality is your badass strength.

you are beloved.

#orlandopride #pulse #49 #clergyabuse #metoo #menow #magical #goldflame #risetogether
#onelove
#ptsd #cptsd #cheerleader

text: i had the privilege of attending the #internationaldayofthegirl luncheon hosted by @girlsincpnw. the energy in the room was absolutely electric and seeing the young girls that have gained so much confidence through this program was inspiring. we still have a long way to go as a society for girls and women to feel free to move through the world without fear. did you know 1 in 4 girls under the age of 18 have experienced sexual violence?? if that stat doesn’t wake people up, i’m not sure what will. this statistic represents one of the barriers that females face as they navigate the world. when our confidence is stripped away from sexual assault and sexual harassment, how are we supposed to live up to our fullest potential? i urge you to research the work that @girlsincpnw does to work toward eliminating these barriers for the young girls that are our future, and i thank my amazing company #banfieldlife for giving me the opportunity to attend this inspiring program today. #girlstoo #girlsinc #metoo #enough

text: i think women are typically too hard on each other and that's something we should all work on. but i was extremely disappointed watching melania trump's interview. she wanted to say "she supports women" yet she wouldn't say she supports the #metoo movement. then she says that a woman should only come forward if she has "hard evidence"?!?! is that a joke?! so women are responsible for their own assault investigations now too??? wow, i guess going from first lady michelle obama, the height of class, grace and morality, now we have slumped to the "trump" version of 1st lady. she openly admitted she is more concerned for the boys and men than for the women of this country. a very sad day for survivors and women alike. step up melania. #resist #dumpthetrumps #resistance #womenempowerment #feminism #supportwomen #believesurvivors #supportsurvivors #melaniatrump #antitrump #womenbelongintheresistance #vote #voteblue #bluewave

text:
i deserve to be loved.
even on the days that i feel like i'm not good enough.
even on the days that i make mistakes. 
even on the days where i'm not all dolled up.
even on the days that i am told no one could ever love me.
even on the days my depression and anxiety are difficult for myself, and anyone around me to face.
even on the days where i am bawling on the floor because that dog died in that movie.
i deserve to be loved every day of the week. unconditionally. no exceptions... and those who cannot provide me with such love can politely piss off. 🖕🖕🖕 #ideserve #love #confidence #bodypositive #happy #strength #metoo #effyourbeautystandards #goodenough #pride #selfish #knowyourworth

text:
“your purpose is hidden within your wounds.”
-rune lazuli .
.
.
i have no idea who rune is... but he knows what i have learned so deeply. .
.
.
there is so much depth, purpose, light and strength that is hidden within the trauma of abuse. .
.
.
our wounds can sometimes overtake us. they can paralyze us, hide us, feel as though the walls are caving in and the darkness will win. .
.
.
but this is what i know. you my friend have the light within you. as you begin to search for it, the darkness will fade. just as it does when the sun rises each morning. and as your light grows, your wounds will heal. .
.
.
be strong my friends. your warrior strength is emerging. 🙏🏻

text:
about last night... je suis déconcertée.
je suis allée danser hier soir.
j'adore danser.
et j'adore danser seule.
faire la con avec mes potes,m'amuser.
danser.

il m'arrive de danser avec des mecs mais...seulement si j'ai #envie
je préfère clairement danser seule qu'avec le stéréotype du relou bourré qui vient te demander pour la 30e fois de danser avec toi et pour qui ton #non n'est pas une réponse.

je fais ce que je veux,n'est ce pas?

pourtant hier soir,un mec m'a agressée parce qu'il en avait décidé autrement!
mettant ses mains sur mon cul,essayant de fourrer sa langue dans ma bouche!?!
disant qu'il allait me baiser bien tranquillement!? est ce que tu embrasses ta mère avec cette bouche garçon?
parce qu'elle en contient de la merde!
et ta mère?...elle aurait sans doûte eu envie de pleurer si elle t'avait vu!

qu'est ce qui est difficile à comprendre dans le mot #non
3 putains de lettres... quel honneur tires tu d'essayer d'embrasser quelqu'un de force?
de plaquer quelqu'un,de force,
contre toi?
garder sur la peau l'odeur de ton parfum dégueulasse..
nausée

comme on peut voir sur cette photo,ça manquait pas de filles qui avait envie de se faire du bien hier soir..
alors pourquoi aller voir celle qui dit #non ?
je me suis rasée la tête aussi pour me protéger,mettre une distance avec les hommes..
mais en fait... #échec 
ya des chacals que rien n'arrête.

je pense à celles, fragiles, bourrées,qui ne disent pas non assez fort...
je pense à tous les hommes que ce genre de petite merde dessert car c'est parfois tellement plus simple de généraliser.
je suis #blasée..et en #colère..
car je sais que je suis physiquement plus faible qu'un homme... je suis reconnaissante parce que hier soir,je n'étais pas seule,j'avais des amis avec moi..mais si ça n'avait pas été le cas?
le pire c'est que ce genre de #comportement est totalement banal!et c'est clairement pas la 1ere fois de ma vie que ça m'arrive.
et sous pretexte de boite, d'alcool, de contexte, on aurait presque tendance à se dire qu'on l'a presque cherché..
après tout c'est vrai..j'ai qu'à pas aller bouger mon boule sur un dancefloor !?! en attendant..je suis #toujoursdebout
#femme #homme #metoo #balancetonporc

don’t let your eyes be blinded by her beauty.this is my town.this is the most magical pic of your life.#metoo

text:
warning: sexual assault/harassment/rape

i was 14 and a girl came into my life. she quickly turned into my best friend. i knew i’d be alone without her, and i hated that. but she slowly started telling me how i looked fat. she would make me clean her house because it was “the least i could do for her to allow me in her home.” i didn’t mind cleaning, it was the words that hurt. then, she started to restrict what i ate, what i drank, insult me for how unfit i was, and tell me i was worthless, unlovable, gross. i started self harming again, and she told me to go deeper next time. it got physical. i let it happen, because god, i didn’t want to be alone. one night i was sleeping over at her house. it was hot in her room, so she made me change into one of her bras, and stay in only that and pants. she did the same. i was very uncomfortable, but didn’t want to upset her. multiple times that night, she exposed herself to me, because she was sending pictures to guys. eventually, she got tired and asked me to send pictures instead. i said no, that i was uncomfortable. after a while of debating, she pulled my left bra strap down and starting feeling my chest. i don’t remember how long i sat there before i pulled away and asked what the hell she was doing. she promised she’d stop if i just took the picture, so i did. i threw her phone at her, and i guess i hurt her, because she slapped me across the face before going to bed. i listened to champagne supernova by oasis to calm me down after. i can’t listen to that song anymore without feeling sick. #metoo #nomore #metoomovement
name: #metoo

text:
it’s good to remind yourself that you are enough; that just being you is enough! change is apart of life and is a good thing, but never let anyone tell you that the core of you and who you are needs to change because it does not need to change!! i am driven, passionate, caring, competitive, sarcastic, witty, loving, hardworking, serious and stubborn. i show my love in many ways and i won’t/can’t change that. i care a lot! maybe too much but that is me and i love me! i’ve learned that i love me and that i can’t change my core or want to. some people can’t handle how i show my feelings, but that’s just not the people i’m meant to have in my life. i just want you to know that being you is always okay and to never ever think that it’s not. mature and grow but never change who you are! •

text:
the #metoo movement has resulted in sweeping new laws in many states and california is not an exception. governor brown has been busy signing new laws expanding protections against harassment and discrimination. more specifically:
employers may now be liable for any guest or patron harassment, not just sexual harassment. in other words, if a guest harasses an employee based on any protected class, an employer may be liable if it is aware of the harassment and fails to take appropriate corrective action.
sexual harassment training requirements have been expanded to any employer with 5 or more employees. this new requirement starts in 2020.
settlement agreements related to certain sex offenses may no longer include a confidentiality provision.
lactation accommodations have changed and now specifically state that a toilet stall is not acceptable. 
if you have any other questions, please do not hesitate to contact us directly.
name: Stokes Wagner

sexual harassment training requirements have been expanded to any employer with 5 or more employees. this new requirement stas in 2020.
settlement agreements related to ceain sex offenses may no longer include a confidentiality provision.
lactation accommodations have changed and now specifically state that a toilet stall is not acceptable. 
if you have any other questions, please do not hesitate to contact us directly.

appreciation post:

text:
in support of the #metoo movement that is spreading across india i would like to share my short encounter with bollywood. firstly, hats off to the women and men that are stepping up and whistleblowing.
-
after winning miss canada and placing as a finalist at miss universe i was offered roles in indian films and various ad campaigns. super excited about my new career i left my country and packed my bags… landing in mumbai full of gusto and big plans!
-
within the first few months i was asked point blank if i was willing to sleep with the producers. i was shocked. it was bluntly stated that there are movie offers but they want to know if i would be willing to sleep with them first. part of me was shocked but most of me was scared. 😳 
i responded defensively that i’m an educated woman from a good family and would never do that… he said that’s what they all say in the beginning (and disclosed names of many a-list actresses). i was so disgusted and disheartened from the whole encounter that i packed my bags and said goodbye to my bollywood dreams.
-
i never told my parents, community or collogues why i abruptly stopped my launch into the movie business and changed paths. i was so ashamed of the experience even though it had nothing to do with me. i felt powerless that i couldn’t work towards my goals without compromising my values, which i refused to do. and i couldn’t believe something like this could happen in india, a place where family values and spirituality rule... but it does and it needs to stop.
-
i love mumbai and know many actresses that have had a great run in bollywood and thankfully didn’t experience hassarssment. it’s just unfortunate that so many dreams are crushed, and women (and men) victimized in such a vibrant and creative industry.
-
i want to give a shout out to all the courageous people who are supporting this movement with their voices and sharing their stories. it’s about time india! 👊🏼🇮🇳
-

text:
du har sikkert hørt uttrykket om «elefanten i rommet»? dvs. den åpenbare sannhet som ikke nevnes, som ingen vil snakke om, men som alle vet eksisterer. jeg vokste opp med flere store elefanter, og i mesteparten av livet har jeg ikke turt å snakke om det som skjedde med meg. som 8-åring prøvde jeg å stå opp mot urett som ble gjort mot en person jeg fortsatt er glad i... jeg varslet om det jeg hadde sett, men ble ikke trodd. jeg ble kalt en løgner av min stefar og min egen mor, fordi alle for en hver pris ville dekke over denne uretten, dette overgrepet som jeg hadde vært vitne til. dere sa jeg bare hadde funnet på alt sammen, at jeg fantaserte. fra det øyeblikket ble jeg til det vanskelige barnet. jenta som ikke ville føye seg, jenta som var så lik far sin, og den jævla slekta der... senere samme år ble jeg selv utsatt for overgrep for første gang, og det har siden preget meg hele livet. i dag har jeg valgt åpenheten, fordi taushet er så mye vondere. den gang da visste jeg at jeg ikke kunne si noe, for jeg hadde allerede erfart at min mor ikke trodde meg. jeg mistet meg selv den natten. jeg kan neste ikke beskrive hva jeg følte. kanskje en slags lammelse? jeg var så ung, bare 8 år. jeg skulle ønske at den voksne heidi, kunne si til barnet heidi: «det kommer til å gå bra til slutt, men du må selv male elefanten rosa for at den skal bli synlig. ingen andre kommer til å gjøre det for meg». kanskje jeg da hadde turt å være åpen mye tidligere? elefanten på bildet synes jeg er like befriende vakker, som det å plassere skylden der den hører hjemme, har vært for meg. strål som faen — for du vet aldri hvem som trenger akkurat ditt lys ❤️
.

name: Heidi Irene Arstad
tweet_full:
du har sikkert hørt uttrykket om «elefanten i rommet»? dvs. den åpenbare sannhet som ikke nevnes, som ingen vil snakke om, men som alle vet eksisterer. jeg vokste opp med flere store elefanter, og i mesteparten av livet har jeg ikke turt å snakke om det som skjedde med meg. som 8-åring prøvde jeg å stå opp mot urett som ble gjort mot en person jeg fortsatt er glad i... jeg varslet om det jeg hadde sett, men ble ikke trodd. jeg ble kalt en løgner av min stefar og min egen mor, fordi alle for en hver pris ville dekke over denne uretten, dette overgrepet som jeg hadde vært vitne til. dere sa jeg bare hadde funnet på alt sammen, at jeg fantaserte. fra det øyeblikket ble jeg til det vanskelige barnet. jenta som ikke ville føye seg, jenta som var så lik far sin, og den jævla slekta der... senere samme år ble jeg selv utsatt for overgrep for første gang, og det har siden preget meg hele livet. i dag har jeg valgt åpenheten, fordi taushet er så mye vondere. den gang da visste jeg at jeg ikke kunne si noe, for jeg hadde allerede erfart at min mor ikke trodde meg. jeg mistet meg selv den natten. jeg kan neste ikke beskrive hva jeg følte. kanskje en slags lammelse? jeg var så ung, bare 8 år. jeg skulle ønske at den voksne heidi, kunne si til barnet heidi: «det kommer til å gå bra til slutt, men du må selv male elefanten rosa for at den skal bli synlig. ingen andre kommer til å gjøre det for meg». kanskje jeg da hadde turt å være åpen mye tidligere? elefanten på bildet synes jeg er like befriende vakker, som det å plassere skylden der den hører hjemme, har vært for meg. strål som faen — for du vet aldri hvem som trenger akkurat ditt lys ❤️
.

text:
last night was brutal. i completely lost my 💩 on the phone with my parents. between having a dear friend dying of lung cancer, dealing with difficult student behaviors at school, and a lot of additional stress, i just popped when politics were brought up and non-solutions kept being suggested for solving real problems when all i needed was someone to listen and empathize. i loudly and weepingly shared my semi-recent #metoo story that i had never shared with my parents to try to get them to see things from another perspective. i definitely didn’t plan on sharing and certainly didn’t mean for my kids to overhear me. lots of hugging and crying here last night... ugh. i am still a little upset and i dropped way too many f-bombs over the last 24 hours. 
anyway- i didn’t do my 31 day challenge evening check in last night (though my meals were 💯) or workout and take a flex friday picture this morning, because i still felt so hollow and exhausted. i did, however, have quite a nice day with my class today. my son and i had a relaxing evening together with a cozy fire in the fireplace while decorating for halloween and watching the newest star wars movie. my sweet husband took our daughter and her friends to a haunted house and hayride this evening. i planned to make soup in the crockpot, but that didn’t happen either. grocery store sushi and spring rolls worked, but i’m definitely ready to put the last 24 hours behind me. .
.
just keeping it real, friends. i don’t want to just share my life’s highlight reel.

anyway- i didn’t do my 31 day challenge evening check in last night (though my meals were 💯) or workout and take a flex friday picture this morning, because i still felt so hollow and exhausted. i did, however, have quite a nice day with my class today. my son and i had a relaxing evening together with a cozy fire in the fireplace while decorating for halloween and watching the newest star wars movie. my sweet husband took our daughter and her friends to a haunted house and hayride this evening. i planned to make soup in the crockpot, but that didn’t happen either. grocery store sushi and spring rolls worked, but i’m definitely ready to put the last 24 hours behind me. .
.
just keeping it real, friends. i don’t want to just share my life’s highlight reel.

text: i am feeling tired and sad and angry. as one writer put it, there is a volcano now simmering out in the american kitchen and office and bedroom and garden. to paraphrase, for i have lost the original, women knew what was going to happen with kavanaugh, we knew and yet we still spoke up and now we are angry and lighting a fire with our determination, our voices, our anger. but i want to remember to also fuel that fire with the things i know to be the fuel of revolution, the long-burning matches of change and integration and balance-of creating a society that lives in integrity. those things are love and compassion, vulnerability and forgiveness. the strongest of strengths, the most super of superpowers. my sweet dog calypso reminds me of this when she throws herself down on the sand, in utter joy, completely vulnerable, unencumbered by worry or rage or disappointment on a grand scale. so for today, or for an hour, i will put down my anger and rest in the space that is love and light and faith that we will overcome. i choose, for this moment, to rise up with joy. #riseup #womenempowerment #lovehard #findthegood #bethegood #kindness #compassion #forgiveness #turningofthetide #timesup #believesurvivors #findjoy #drchristineblaseyford #metoo

text:
social platforms are taken by  storm with this #metoomovement 
and i've been meaning to write this for quite a while now.
but i didn't want to put up a rant that tells you things you're already aware of.
instead of hiding in our lives, being a  clueless bunch as always, fickling our way through any social reform. i want us to react to this in a better way.

thinking of it as a facade when some accusations turn out to be false.
thinking of it as empowering and righteous, when they stand valid.

it's almost like you don't have an opinion of your own, almost like you don't believe in anything.
well, i'll tell you what you should believe in.
believe her!

believe her, when she says she was touched without her consent.
believe her, when she says some of those texts she received last night from were inappropriate.
believe her, when she says she doesn't feel safe in this world full of immoral, deluded, inhuman pieces of trash who think they can get away with whatever shit they torment women with.
believe her, for the women that you know could be similar victims, lacking the courage this entire time, to voice their horrors.

now, some of you might still ask "but how do i know this movement won't encourage women putting false allegations on men, ruining their lives or careers?"
to those of you, i say (only after a cynical smirk), where were you when they were keeping mum over it?
where was your rational thinking then?
were you expressing your concern when she was slowly  breaking down from within?
were you devastated by the fact that even after years, when she was old enough, strong enough, she could never speak up about it? 
i'm guessing "yes" isn't the most recurring answer.
so "no", you don't get to play this card.
and them on the other hand, they've just recently been dealt a fair hand.

so don't try to silence them all, just because one of those voices could be ingenuine. 
chances are, and by saying chances i'm being really modest here because surely is the word, this is still just a handful of them. 
i'd believe in these handful everyday till all of them know, that it's not okay to face such terrible things, that they're not alone in this.
so should you~

text:
hey friends i am on this panel organized by dr. gail levin @gail.levin.art , #metoo in the art world at @nationalartsclub , nyc, oct.23rd at 6:30pm. would love to see you if you care about the problem and want to be part of the evening!
#kathygoodellart #artworldproblems #womensrights #sexualassault#workplacediscrimination #academicenvironment #artschooldiscrimination

the #metoo movement and the art world at
the national arts club, nyc
moderated by dr. gail levin

tuesday, october 23rd, 6:30pm
atoa will be hosting its 2nd panel discussion of the 2018-2019 season with a focus on how the #metoo movement is impacting the art world and the lives of artists. coming on the cusp of the midterm elections and the confirmation of justice kavanaugh, this panel could not be more pertinent to our times or lives.
panel: suzanne anker, chair, bfa fine arts department, school of visual arts; nancy azara, american sculptor; kathy goodell, new york painter and sculptor. 
moderator: dr. gail levin, an american art historian, biographer, artist and a distinguished professor of art history, american studies, women's studies, and liberal studies at baruch college and the graduate center of the city university of new york.
organized by douglas i. sheer, chair atoa and dr. gail levin.
for more information: http://www.atoa.org/fall2018/october.htm#10/23
the national arts club, 15 gramercy park south (east 20th street)

text:
“we claim to live in a body-loving era, but diet culture is rife and western society therefore largely ignores women’s continuing and pervasive feelings of bodily deficiency in our culture of appearances. it has become sadly common for women to find themselves lacking as they measure themselves against the idealized images of the thin, computer-generated femininity found in mainstream culture or the skinny celebrities touting appetite-suppressant lollipops. as susan bordo explains in her introduction to twilight zones, we have become accustomed to “a visual iconography of the perfected body” and as a result, women today are concerned with the shape of their bodies as a primary expression of their individual identity.” -francesca king  if we, women, honestly think about it, we are all slaves to diet culture. i find myself jumping in and out of it on a regular basis. when will we shake off societies’ shackles and scream “enough is enough! i am more than my body!” when will we stop criticizing each other, believe survivors, and stop looking for reasons to envy or hate each other? i’m tired, aren’t you? .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text: i’m about to rant so get ready // i’ve been going through a lot myself recently,,,depression has been beating my buns, all these life changes. going from being a family unit to single mom is a lot more rough than it looks,,especially when the relationship itself was not healthy to begin with. one of the hardest things to do was to stand up for myself and let go of someone who was toxic. i was too blind to see it because i was too close to situation. but the more i distance myself i start to really see. my daughter and i deserve to be treated better than what we were receiving,,,we don’t deserve to be abused in any way. i will not let myself be manipulated anymore. #rant #mentalhealth #metoo #depressionawareness #selfcare #kawaii #anime #funimation #likeforlike #like4like #souleater #blair #cats #edit #aesthetic #aesthetictumblr #tumblrgirl #rainy #spoopy #love #selflove

text: what an amazing, inspiring, empowering and motivating day! it’s so important to come together, to be supportive and advocate for one another. change doesn’t happen unless we speak up, unless we challenge the status quo. it’s 2018.. and women are still making $0.80 for every $1.00 a man makes. 99% of domestic violence cases involve financial  issues at home. women are under represented in senior leadership roles.. so much to think about and consider. plus all the wisdom and insight regarding career development, managing “up” - personal brand, getting paid what your worth and personal insight into breaking the glass ceiling. words can’t really describe today but i’m so thankful for this experience. #blessed #pennwomen #metoo #speakup #inclusion #diversity #womenempowerment #careerdevelopment

text:
something i haven't talked about in a long time, but i feel like right now is an important time to. 7 years ago i was in an abusive relationship. i was also sexually assaulted by this person a few times. why didn't i say anything? why didn't i leave? because he threatened to kill me. one day i finally convinced myself and him to end things because we were so unhappy and i was finally released. it was only 6 months, but i was very unhappy during that time. i lost a lot of weight and still felt fat and ugly. all because of him. now i'm with someone who treasures me. i never worry about being hurt or cheated on or unloved. a lot happened in that short time. but i am stronger for it and not afraid to talk about it like i was for over a year after it ended. i hope others start stepping up and being brave enough to share their story.
#abusesurvivor #strongwoman #imnotafraid #notavictim #survivor #proud #metoo #shareyourstory

text:
||| a star is born movie review (7/10).🎵
..
1) overview:
..
where shall i begin. well the movie kicks off with bradley cooper so let's start there. this talented actor has proved that the director's hat suites him perfectly with this debut. lady gaga - she did her lead perfectly. i suppose every supporting actor especially sam elliot has done exceptional work. sam elliot's character comes on screen for a few scenes maybe,  but there were times when he had complete dominance over the audience even with the company of bradley. that's how good he was.
there is this one little scene where he has to look back and drive his car, he had me and everybody's heart right there.
everybody had great chemistry and a major contributing factor was the dialogues of the film. right on note🎵!
..
2) direction:
..
the story of the film is one that has been presented to the same audience multiple times. but when this film sung🎵 it over again, it had a drastically different vibe🎵. it's true, bradley cooper might just win an oscar for his directorial debut or he might just win 2, one for the former and one for his exceptional portrayal of a drunk - drug addicted - dried out - ageing singer. ..
..
3) songs:
..
i had noted that every song in the film had great lyrics and were wonderfully composed. have to download it now😑
..
⭕ verdict: watch it in theaters, if you want to absorb the heart of the film. "a hollywood love story"
..
the movie sheds light on the entertainment industry too. about how people are categorized and pulled into the business by influential stars based on emotional & physical connections #metoo #moment (7/10)..

text:
el abuso sexual es un tema de agenda esta semana, y decidi contar mi historia abiertamente porque quiza mis palabras le sirvan a otra persona para empezar a hablar de lo que no se habla, decir lo que no se dice por miedo al rechazo o la estigmatización. es cierto que algunas marcas nunca se van, principalmente las que surgen en la infancia, pero tambien es cierto que hasta el dolor mas desgarrador puede transformarse en algo positivo. a través de esta experiencia aprendi a superar obstáculos, a seguir mis sueños sin bajar los brazos, a no tomar nada como algo personal, a perdonar y pedir perdon, a dejar ir lo que no es para mi, a valorar cada logro por pequeño que sea, a encontrar soluciones donde otros ven problemas, a creer que no todos los hombres son iguales, a disfrutar del sexo libremente y sin prejuicios, a creer en el amor en todas sus formas, a respetar el dolor ajeno, a no quedar atrapada en el lugar de víctima y ser la protagonista de mi propia vida. pero fundamentalmente, encontré mi misión en el mundo que es trasmitir todo este aprendizaje a otras mujeres. en definitiva, no importa lo que haya pasado, nosotrxs somos los unicxs responables de nuestras circunstancias. empoderate!  #womanpower

text: do not expect anything if you ask a question or offer a girl (stranger) whether she wants to smoke and then she replies politely, “no, thank you.” she just has a good manner to reply a human being politely (avoid the guy to get mad as well). talking to stranger is ok but it is not ok when you (guys) think that the girl is interested in you. it is just a public talk or conversation (or just answering in order to avoid humiliate you by not replying anything). this is a part of my story tonight in the metro in the north of france. i replied politely back to a stranger who offered me to smoke (in the metro/train). i rejected nicely but he thinks i am friendly. i am ok with complement. he kept asking me things but i avoided to answer (home information or country of origin) in order to stop the conversation. then, he attempted to kiss me by asking whether i know “french kiss” or not and bending himself towards me. i reacted quickly with my arms to block him and i switched from the nice to aggressive mode by threatening him to put him in jail and call a police (thanks to the new french law about harassment. i think i will have to print this law out in french and give to any stranger guys who tried to talk to me without a respect manner.) #metoo
